    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-11-10T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-11-10T20:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660m.11212/a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Lithuania</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-10T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1928—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Consul at Kovno reports certificates of origin required under amended
                    Lithuanian Tariff. It is not clear whether or not new Lithuanian regulations
                    will give rise to difficulties, particularly with reference to shipments of
                    American goods from third countries, such as arose in connection with Latvian
                    regulations. Please consult Consul and if necessary endeavor to work out with
                    Lithuanian Government arrangement similar to that effected with Latvia as
                    reported by your telegram 62, July 7, 1928, (noon)<note n="5" xml:id="d228fn5"
                        >Not printed.</note> and your <pb facs="0398" n="288" xml:id="pg_288"/>
                    despatch 5439 July 10, 1928.<note n="6" xml:id="d228fn6">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_232">p. 232</ref>.</note>
                    Specimen certificates for grain lard fatbacks et cetera are being mailed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
